trajectory.actor_reasoning:
Using the LibreTexts Introductory Chemistry (CK-12, Alviar-Agnew & Agnew) density table: honey 1.420 g/mL and mayonnaise 0.910 g/mL.
- Start with one gallon each; one gallon = sixteen cups.
- Initial extra mass of honey over mayonnaise per gallon: (1.420 − 0.910) × Vg.
- Each cup removed from honey decreases its mass by 1.420 × Vc.
- Need n cups so that 1.420 Vg − n × 1.420 Vc < 0.910 Vg ⇒ n > (0.510/1.420) × (Vg/Vc) = (0.510/1.420) × 16 ≈ 5.746.
- Minimum whole cups: 6.

FINAL ANSWER: 6

messages.content:
Using the LibreTexts Introductory Chemistry (CK-12, Alviar-Agnew & Agnew) density table: honey 1.420 g/mL and mayonnaise 0.910 g/mL.
- Start with one gallon each; one gallon = sixteen cups.
- Initial extra mass of honey over mayonnaise per gallon: (1.420 − 0.910) × Vg.
- Each cup removed from honey decreases its mass by 1.420 × Vc.
- Need n cups so that 1.420 Vg − n × 1.420 Vc < 0.910 Vg ⇒ n > (0.510/1.420) × (Vg/Vc) = (0.510/1.420) × 16 ≈ 5.746.
- Minimum whole cups: 6.

FINAL ANSWER: 6
